                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1v">Fol. 1v</locus>: Record concerning reconciliation.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 1v: የሽበቃ፡ ሃድጉ፡ ልጅ፡ ና፡ የኀይታና፡ ሐማር፡ ልጅ፡ ገደለች፡ ኛ፡ ሲታረቁ፡…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written in Amharic, during the time of šum ʾagame Kasa (governor of ʾAgame in 1914-18, 1941-48), by Gäbrä Ḥǝywät (of) Mayraza (probably May Raza Täklä Haymanot, THMR).
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#2r">Fol. 2r</locus>: Prohibition to transgress the church’s property rights (concerning the donation of fitawrari Ḥaylä Mikaʾel?).<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 2r: በ፲፱፻፲፩፡ ዓመተ፡ ምህረት፡ ዘወሐቦ፡ ፊታውራሪ፡ ሐይለ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ጊዎርጊስ፡ ጎናይ፡…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written in the year of mercy 1911 (= 1918/19 A.D.) Pen trial in the first two lines written in the same hand as the main text; the prohibition note is added in a later hand.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#13r">Fol. 13r</locus>: Donation note<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 13r: ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘደጅ፡ አዝማች፡ ሰብአ፡ ጋዲስ፡ ዘወሀባ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ዘመነቦት፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መርሀ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ልዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in the same hand as the name Zä-Mänfäs Qǝddus in the supplication formulas.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The word śäyṭan "devil" is written upside down, in the main text, on fols. 14v, 65v.&#xD;
- The scribe reduced the size of his handwriting to accommodate the end of the line on many fols.: fols. 22r, 25v, 27v, 68v.&#xD;
- The scribe used compressed script: fols. 65v, 76v.&#xD;
- Omitted letters and words are inserted interlineally or written in the margin, in very small script: e.g., fols. 13v, 16r, 25r, 59r, 63r, 89r, 109r.&#xD;
- Corrections written over erasures on many fols.: e.g., fols. 5r, 10v, 17r, 60r, 73v, 83v.&#xD;
- Erasures marked with thin lines: fols. 12r, 18r, 24r, 52v.&#xD;
- Erasures marked with frame: fols. 37r, 38r, 38v.&#xD;
- Erasures: fols. 33r, 34r, 79r, 88r, 99v.&#xD;
- Pen trials, scribbles and doodles: fols.: 1r, 2r, 2v, 31r, 36r, 44r, 44v, 56v, 75r, 83r.</item>
                     </list>
